## 2. Modèle de données — table `notifications`

```sql
-- supabase/migrations/xxxx_notifications.sql
create type notification_type as enum (
  'booking_created',
  'booking_cancelled',
  'booking_confirmed',
  'order_paid',
  'order_shipped',
  'order_refunded',
  'new_message',
  'new_review',
  'payment_failed',
  'stripe_payout',
  'system'
);

create table public.notifications (
  id          uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id     uuid not null references auth.users(id) on delete cascade,
  type        notification_type not null,
  title       text not null,
  body        text not null,
  link        text,                            -- URL relative : /dashboard/orders/123
  metadata    jsonb not null default '{}'::jsonb,
  read_at     timestamptz,
  created_at  timestamptz not null default now()
);

create index notifications_user_unread_idx
  on public.notifications (user_id, created_at desc)
  where read_at is null;

create index notifications_user_created_idx
  on public.notifications (user_id, created_at desc);
```

`metadata jsonb` permet d'attacher du contexte sans altérer le schéma :
`order_id`, `booking_id`, `amount`, `ai_score`, etc.

